frameDefinitions: This frame is for words that denote highly schematic entities.
A Communicator conveys a Message to an Addressee; the Topic and Medium of the communication also may be expressed.
A Cause triggers a System to operate in accordance with its intended purpose.
A Possible_event is deemed to have all pre-conditions satisfied; in other words, it has some probability of occurrence, if some (generally implicit) further Condition pertains.
A Supplier gives a Theme to a Recipient to fulfill a need or purpose (Imposed_purpose) of the Recipient.
This frame concerns permanent organizations (the Institutions) that are intended to help members of the Target_group in a particular Domain with a Service_action.
frameExamples: We found an unusual wooden <t>object</t> in the desert.
Let's hope it did n't have time to <t>communicate</t> any of its findings to its overlords.
Smoking a cigarette will normally not <t>set off</t> a smoke alarm.
Habituating the ground nesting chimp groups is done by <t>provisioning</t> them with sugar cane. CNI INI
The Red Cross Tracing and Message Service is a <t>service</t> for finding and reuniting families separated by war and disaster.
listRoleDefinitions: A thing (either abstract or physical) that exists with some degree of permanence.
The sentient entity that uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey a <fen>Message</fen> to the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
<fen>Message</fen> is a proposition or set of propositions that the <fen>Communicator</fen> wants the <fen>Addressee</fen> to believe or take for granted.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject matter to which the <fen>Message</fen> pertains. It is normally expressed as a PP Complement headed by 'about', but in some cases it can appear as a direct object.
The physical or abstract setting in which the <fen>Message</fen> is conveyed.
The time at which the communication takes place.
The location where the act of communication occurs.
The <fen>Cause</fen> interacts with the <fen>System</fen> such that conditions are met for the <fen>System</fen> to operate.
The <fen>System</fen> interacts with or detects the <fen>Cause</fen> and activates.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.
The time when the triggering takes place.
Where the triggering takes place.
The <fen>Possible_event</fen> has met its preconditions, and will occur if some further <fen>Condition</fen> holds.
The state-of-affairs that does not hold, but if it did, the <fen>Possible_event</fen> would occur.
The time at which the <fen>Possible_event</fen> can occur.
The person that begins in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen> and causes it to be in the possession of the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The object that is given to the <fen>Recipient</fen> .
The <fen>Recipient</fen>'s intended purpose for the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Supplier</fen> gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Supplier</fen> gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
A permanent organization with a socially important purpose.
The concern of the <fen>Institution</fen>-- broadly speaking, the aspect of society that they affect.
The members of the public whom the <fen>Institution</fen> is intended to serve.
The action performed or enabled by the <fen>Institution</fen> for the <fen>Target_group</fen>.
